It's been over a week since Shepherd and Mary Bushiri fled the country to Malawi. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - The state prosecutor in Malawi plans to appeal Shepherd and Mary Bushiri's release from prison. The couple fled to their home country last week, saying they feared for their lives. READ: Bushiri's R5,5m Centurion property forfeited to the state They were arrested in Malawi, but have since been released. Meanwhile, the justice department in South Africa says it plans to serve an extradition letter on Malawi within the next two weeks. eNCA's Tshegohaco Moagi has more details in the video above.